<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, Christopher Sign Agreement on Radiation Study </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401152994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1509 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Veronika Romanenkova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev and U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher 
have signed here today, after the third round of the 
Russo-American summit talks, an agreement on cooperation in 
studying radiation after-effects with a view to minimise 
radioactive pollution hazards to human health and the 
environment. 
  The purpose of this document is to lay the foundations for 
close and long-term cooperation in studying radiation hazards to 
human health and to the environment. 
  Russia and the United States will jointly study the 
aftermaths of the exposure of humans to ionising radiations, 
will organise the collection and processing of data on radiation 
hazards, will study the environment, and will conduct 
corresponding scientific research. 
  A joint coordination committee will be set up to study the 
after-effects of radiation. The document notes that the sides 
shall ensure an adequate and effective protection of 
intellectual property, created or handed over under the current 
agreement, and conclude corresponding accords on its 
implementation. 
  The agreement will remain in force for five years, subject 
to 
repeated prolongation for the same term. 

</TEXT>

