<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Official Dinner' Held for Clinton 14 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Further on `Official' Kremlin Dinner </H4>
<F P=102> LD1401202494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1950 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- An official dinner in 
honor of U.S. President Bill Clinton and his wife Hillary was 
given tonight in candlelight in the Kremlin's Palace of Facets 
by President Boris Yeltsin and his wife Naina. 
  The presidents and their wives were seated at the central 
table near U.S. State Secretary Warren Christopher, Russian 
Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and his wife. 
  A toast of Boris Yeltsin noted history has given to Russia 
and the United States a unique chance to make their great 
possibilities come true. The Russian president raised the toast 
to welfare and prosperity of the two peoples. He congratulated 
the U.S. guests with New Year marked today on the Orthodox 
calendar. 
  In his turn, Bill Clinton wished the Russian people and 
president health and happiness. 
  The dinner offered champagne, Stolichnaya Vodka, Armenian 
cognacs, white and red wines, Russian cuisine, including caviar, 
salmon and shchi, Russian cabbage soup. 
  The official dinner finished with a concert of choreographic 
and music groups of Russia in Kremlin's St. George Hall. 

</TEXT>

