<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Gives Farewell Address to President Clinton </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1501071894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 0625 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1501071894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Speech by President Boris Yeltsin at a farewell ceremony </F>
for U.S. President Bill Clinton at the Kremlin in Moscow-- live] 
  [Text] Esteemed Mr. President of the United States, 
esteemed Mrs. Clinton, esteemed members of the U.S. delegation: 
  The first official visit by the U.S. President to Russia is 
drawing to a close. I want to express my opinion that this 
visit has been extremely successful. It has demonstrated once 
again that we must indeed be partners and must deepen that 
partnership. We must indeed live together on this small planet 
and try to ensure peace and security, not only in our two 
countries but throughout the world. 
  I thank you, Mr. President, for taking advantage of the 
opportunity and for getting to know the people of Russia, the 
people of Moscow--in the streets, in shops, at Ostankino, and in 
other places--and for seeing for yourself that the people want 
reform and for seeing that the people want freedom and democracy. 
  I think that you have obtained a better knowledge of the 
people of Russia during the visit, and the people of Russia now 
have a better idea of the President of the United States of 
America. 
  I want to wish you bon voyage on your return journey, 
happiness to your families, and prosperity to America and the 
American people. 

</TEXT>

