<H3> <TI>   TU Leader Satisfied With 14 Jan Talks With Clinton </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401185494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1453 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Chairman of Russia's Independent Union of 
Miners, Aleksandr Sergeyev, told Interfax on Friday that "he is 
satisfied with the discussion that a group of union leaders 
conducted with President Bill Clinton at a formal reception in 
the U.S. ambassador's residence in Moscow on Thursday." 
  In his words, at a brief meeting the sides touched upon the 
problems of the workers' movement in Russia at a time of 
economic reform, international cooperation between free unions, 
and prospects of its development. 
  At the end of the meeting, according to Sergeyev, Clinton 
instructed one of his aides to prepare a detailed report on the 
world trade union movement. 

</TEXT>

