<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Holds News Conference in Moscow 14 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Denies Compensation Rumor </H4>
<F P=102> LD1401133694 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401133694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 
at 1200 GMT on 14 January broadcasts a report by Anton Grishin 
on the news conference given by Ukraine President Leonid 
Kravchuk at Ukraine's Embassy in Moscow today, which contains 
recorded remarks by Kravchuk. 
  Kravchuk says: "I would like to express my satisfaction that 
people have shown understanding of Ukraine's situation and have 
not simply tried to force it to agree -- I really did not want 
to use this expression, but it is being used in some political 
circles -- I mean the idea of exerting pressure, of forcing 
Ukraine to agree. We insisted all the way through that people 
should understand our situation, our position, and we achieved 
this without damaging other states' interests; on the contrary, 
in a way beneficial to other states." 
  Grishin summarizes the agreements signed today, and adds: 
  "Leonid Kravchuk denied outright information that Ukraine is 
to receive $1 billion in compensation for the uranium deal. As 
for the problem of the Black Sea Fleet, the leader of Ukraine 
said that Moscow and Kiev can settle the issue in a way that 
takes account of both sides' interests, and that Ukraine is 
ready for dialogue." 

</TEXT>

