<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Holds News Conference in Moscow 14 Jan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Warns of Danger of Zhirinovskiy </H4>
<F P=102> LD1401213294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1702 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401213294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk has drawn 
attention to the danger presented by the political movement 
headed by the leader of the Liberal Democrats Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy. 
  At a news conference in Ukrainian Embassy in Moscow Friday 
[14 January], Kravchuk recognized that the deputy to the State 
Duma Vladimir Zhirinovskiy had been legitimately elected by 
Russian people, but he called him a dangerous phenomenon from 
the point of view of the concept he declares. 
  The Ukrainian President said that the difference should be 
seen between the declarations of ideas and their implementation. 
He called on the Russian and Ukrainian Democrats to unite to 
nip in the bud the political movement led by Zhirinovskiy, even 
though the movement is already represented in parliament. 
  This movement is dangerous for everybody, not solely for 
Ukraine, said Kravchuk. There is no need to think that only 
Ukraine will be the victim of nationalism if it wins in Russia, 
he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

