<H3> <TI>   Official Reaction to Tripartite Agreement Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Defense Officials Meet </H4>
<F P=102> LD1401222094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1702 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401222094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On Friday in Moscow, Russia's First Deputy Defense 
Minister Andrey Kokoshin and Chief of Russia's General Staff 
Colonel General Mikhail Kolesnikov met with the Ukrainian 
Defense Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy. 
  The Russian Defense Ministry's Information and Press 
Department told INTERFAX that in the course of the conversation 
the parties discussed ways to effectively implement agreements 
reached between leaders of the two countries' Defense 
Departments in Moscow and aimed at further development of 
military cooperation between Russia and Ukraine and tripartite 
agreements between Russia, United States, and Ukraine on 
liquidation of nuclear weapons on Ukraine's territory. 
  The discussion was being held in a constructive mood. 

</TEXT>

