<H3> <TI>   Talks With Estonia Postponed; Delegation Head Ill </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701144494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1419 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Krivoshey] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- Russia and Estonia have 
agreed to postpone their talks which were due to resume outside 
Moscow on January 18 until a later date. 
  A Russian Foreign Ministry official said that the talks had 
been postponed because of the illness of the head of the Russian 
delegation. The talks are expected to resume in a week's time. 

</TEXT>

