<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Latvia Opens Consulate in Pskov Oblast </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601145494 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent N. Nedosekina from Pskov; from the "Vesti" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Pskov has become the first oblast in Russia where 
the Latvian Republic has opened its consulate. This is not 
accidental. The whole state border between Russia and Latvia 
goes through Pskov oblast. 
  A lot is being expected from the new consulate. It will make 
it possible for people who have been suddenly divided by state 
borders to preserve kinship and friendly ties. In the past one 
had to travel from the border to St. Petersburg to get a visa. 
  Strengthening economic contacts between Russia and Latvia is 
another important thing. Around 40 joint ventures are operating 
in Pskov oblast alone. 
  Today's event is the first sign. Estonia's consulate and an 
office of the Russian Foreign Ministry are to be opened in Pskov 
in the future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

