<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Navy Denies Sale </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801100094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0335 GMT 
18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press office of the Russian Navy has denied a 
report in a Japanese newspaper [TOKYO SHIMBUN on 16 January]. 
The report says that the Pacific Fleet has sold to North Korea 
four submarines which, after repair, will join the DPRK naval 
forces. The press office of the Russian Navy said that a 
contract had indeed been signed for the sale of 12 obsolete 
diesel submarines with a Japanese firm. However, at present 
these submarines are in a condition which rules out their being 
used for combat purposes. Moreover, Russian experts will be 
monitoring the complete dismantling of the submarines. 

</TEXT>

