<H3> <TI>   Soskovets To Participate in Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801130494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1148 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin began his meeting at 
midday Tuesday [18 January] with Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin. Expected to also take part is first Vice Premier 
Oleg Soskovets. They are to make a final decision on the 
government's new composition. 
  Government sources say that Soskovets, as the first deputy 
prime minister, will continue to be responsible for industry, 
transport, the military-industrial complex, and the fuel and 
energy complex. 
  The meeting of the government commission responsible for 
solving urgent problems, which was planned for Tuesday at 3 
p.m., has been postponed for an indefinite period. The meeting, 
which was to discuss measures on how to stabilize the situation 
in the aluminum industry, investment funds in the power 
industry, and export quotas for 1994, is likely to take place 
next week. 

</TEXT>

