<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yushenkov Says Fedorov Will Resign, Chubays Will Stay </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601163094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1503 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1601163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin took "calmly" 
Yegor Gaydar's decision to resign from the post of first vice 
premier, Sergey Yushenkov, the Russia's Choice secretary, told 
Interfax. 
  Yushenkov announced that on Sunday morning the bureau of the 
Russia's Choice faction had held a meeting with Gaydar's 
participation and unanimously supported Gaydar's decision, aware 
that he could not bear the responsibility for the policy he does 
not support. 
  Yushenkov said that Gaydar would concentrate on his 
parliamentary activity and on the creation of a new party on the 
basis of Russia's Choice. 
  To quote Yushenkov, Finance Minister Boris Fedorov is also 
planning to quit the government. Like Gaydar, "he cannot bear 
the responsibility for a policy which will inevitable spur 
inflation". 
  Anatoliy Chubays will stay in the government, said 
Yushenkov. 
  In the new situation, the parliamentary committee for the 
budget, planning and taxes should be led by Russia's Choice 
representative Aleksandr Pochinok, although earlier Russia's 
Choice had not objected to this committee being led by Grigoriy 
Yavlinskiy's nearest associate Mikhail Zadornov. 

</TEXT>

