<H3> <TI>   Fedorov Announces Conditions for Remaining in Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701205794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1956 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701205794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Boris Fedorov has put the following conditions to 
his joining the government as the minister of finance: 
Aleksandr Zaveryukha should not be the deputy prime minister 
and the president should not confirm Viktor Geraschenko as the 
head of the Central Bank. 
  In a brief interview to the journalists on Monday evening 
[17 
January] in the lobbies of the State Duma B. Fedorov said that 
he had written a letter asking to join the membership of the 
Banking Subcommittee of the Plans and Budget Committee of the 
State Duma. 
  According to B. Fedorov he also made a decision to join the 
Union of December 12 group of deputies headed by the deputy 
premier of the Moscow government Aleksandr Braginsky. 

</TEXT>

