<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaydar Rejects Position of First Deputy Premier </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601101494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to reports from Russian and western news 
agencies, Yegor Gaydar told a briefing in Moscow today that he 
has not accepted the offer of a job as first deputy head of 
government. 
  According to AGENCE FRANCE-PRESSE, he showed journalists a 
letter addressed to the president asking to resign. 
  Yegor Gaydar explains that he is taking this action because 
he finds it difficult to accept responsibility for decisions has 
has not personally made. This refers to disagreements with 
other members of the government over implementation of the 
reforms. 

</TEXT>

