<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gives Reason for Rejecting Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601103194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1007 
GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 16 Jan -- "I have decided to decline an 
offer from the chairman of the government, and am not taking the 
post of first deputy prime minister," Yegor Gaydar said today at 
a meeting with journalists. 
  He said the reason for his position is that decisions have 
recently been taken in the government "in a way in which I took 
no part and with which I categorically disagreed." Yegor Gaydar 
gave just two examples: the signing of an Interbank agreement 
uniting the monetary systems of Russia and Belarus, and also the 
government's decision to construct a new building for parliament 
(the provisional cost of which is nearly $500 million). 
  "I cannot simultaneously be in the government and also in 
the 
opposition. I cannot be responsible for the reforms without 
being able to avert actions like those that have been mentioned 
here and without having the necessary levers to consistently 
pursue an economic policy of whose correctness I am convinced," 
Yegor Gaydar said. "Therefore, I deeply regret that I am forced 
to decline the post of first deputy prime minister that has been 
offered me." 

</TEXT>

