<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Announces Resignation to Journalists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601210094 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1900 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601210094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Sergey Shatunov, including recorded excerpts of </F>
resignation announcement by First Deputy Prime Minister Yegor 
Gaydar to journalists in Moscow today; from the "Novosti" 
newscast] 
  [Excerpt] [Shatunov] [passage omitted] It was precisely the 
wish to concentrate fully on parliamentary work and 
dissatisfaction with recent government decisions and the way the 
council of ministers was functioning in general that prompted 
Yegor Gaydar to make a sensational announcement today. 
  [Gaydar] The government has of late and with increasing 
frequency been adopting decisions with which I was either not 
acquainted or against which I categorically objected. I shall 
cite just two typical examples -- I could cite more. 
  [Shatunov] The first was the decision to expand the ruble 
zone and have a joint monetary system with the Republic of 
Belarus. The second, the decision to build a new parliamentary 
center in the center of the capital. 
  [Gaydar] Accordingly, I have decided to decline the offer 
made to me and not accept the post of first deputy chairman of 
the government in its reorganized form. 
  I know that Social Welfare Minister Ella Aleksandrovna 
Pamfilova has said that in this situation she cannot accept 
responsibility for the social policy being implemented, just as 
I cannot answer for the economic policy being implemented. 
  Today we discussed the issue at the board of our 
parliamentary faction. The board backed our decision and 
expressed its readiness for constructive dialogue and 
cooperation with the government. We are ready to support the 
government in all its constructive initiatives and endeavors. 
We shall continue to support the reform policy pursued by the 
president, but at the same time we must make clear our position 
regarding decisions, the political decisions, which we cannot 
support or adopt. 

</TEXT>

