<H3> <TI>   Kostikov Hopes Resignation Will Be Refused </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601163694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1503 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1601163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yegor Gaydar's possible resignation from the post of 
first vice premier "would seriously weaken the president's 
reformatory flank", the president's Press Secretary Vyacheslav 
Kostikov told Interfax special correspondent Vyacheslav Terekhov 
in an exclusive interview on Sunday [16 January]. 
  Kostikov expressed hope that Boris Yeltsin would not accept 
Gaydar's resignation while the reasons for Gaydar's decisions 
"were not strategic" and that a compromise was possible. 

</TEXT>

