<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Not Surprised </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601130694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1215 
GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 16 Jan -- "Yegor Gaydar's refusal to enter 
the new government was not unexpected for Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin," Valentin Sergeyev, chief of the Russian 
Government's press service, said in an ITAR-TASS interview. The 
first deputy prime minister's decision was already suggested by 
the mere fact that he was elected leader of the Russia's Choice 
parliamentary faction, he added. 
  Touching upon accusations by some democratic parties that 
the 
government will be cut at the expense of its reform wing, 
Valentin Sergeyev stressed: "The government, headed by Viktor 
Chernomyrdin, was, is, and will continue to be a government of 
reform." 

</TEXT>

