<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fedorov Understands Gaydar's Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601135794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1330 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Everyone has been waiting to hear what Russian 
Finance Minister Boris Fedorov has to say in response to Yegor 
Gaydar's announcement that he is quitting -- or rather that he 
is not accepting -- the job of first deputy prime minister. 
  Boris Fedorov said today in an interview with the Ekho 
Moskvy 
radio station that he looks upon Yegor Gaydar's decision with 
understanding. Fedorov called this move the beginning of a 
turning point. 
  As far as he himself is concerned, in the finance minister's 
words, he has not yet received an offer to enter the new 
government. If he does receive one, Fedorov remarked, he will 
reach his decision this Monday or Tuesday. 

</TEXT>

