<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fedorov on `Beginning of Changes' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701085394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0803 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701085394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- Russia's Finance Minister 
Boris Fedorov said he understood First Vice-Premier Yegor 
Gaydar's decision to resign from the government, announced on 
Sunday [16 January]. The government's last decisions indicate 
the "beginning of changes", Fedorov pointed out in an interview 
with the "Echo of Moscow" radio station. 
  "I did not have any advance notice of Yegor Gaydar's 
intention", Fedorov said. 
  He said he had not yet got an invitation to join the 
reshuffled government. If such a proposal is made, he will make 
a decision on Monday or Thursday, Fedorov added. 

</TEXT>

