<H3> <TI>   Other Officials View Resignation of Gaydar </TI></H3>
<H4>   Shokhin Comments </H4>
<F P=102> LD1601195194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1900 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601195194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Yegor Gaydar's statement on his resignation is 
either an emotional step or a tactical manuever. At any rate, 
the reasons he gave are clearly not enough to resign over. This 
is what Russian Deputy Prime Minister Aleksandr Shokhin said 
today in an interview with Interfax. He did not rule out the 
possibility of it simply being an attempt to achieve a 
pro-Gaydar government cabinet. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

