<H3> <TI>   Other Officials View Resignation of Gaydar </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kuzbass Governor Comments </H4>
<F P=102> LD1801092494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0715 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801092494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Grigoriy Shalakin] </F>
  [Text] Kemerovo January 18 TASS -- "Gaydar's resignation 
from the government is expected to indefinitely halt the 
solution of the most difficult problems of Russia's fuel and 
energy complex," said Mikhail Kislyuk, governor of Kuzbass, at a 
meeting with journalists. 
  In his opinion, during a visit to coal regions of the 
country 
at the end of last year Gaydar managed to realise the situation 
in the coal industry after which documents were signed to ease 
critical tension in miners' collectives. A mechanism of 
interaction between the government and miners was found and 
Gaydar took a great deal of responsibility in the realisation of 
this mechanism, Kislyuk said. 
  "The resignation of the first vice-premier makes miners 
doubt 
that their interests will be understood by the government," he 
said. 

</TEXT>

