<H3> <TI>   Yavlinskiy Unaware of Being Possible Gaydar Replacement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601164794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1503 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1601164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Leaders of the Yavlinskiy bloc, prominent economist 
Grigoriy Yavlinskiy told Interfax on Sunday that he knew nothing 
about the possibility of replacing Gaydar in the reorganized 
government. 
  "No one has talked with me about this," he said. The news 
about Yavlinskiy's possible government appointment was revealed 
by Yegor Gaydar during a briefing on Sunday with reference to 
his talks with Prime Minister Chernomyrdin. 
  Asked by Interfax if he would accept such a proposal if it 
were made, Yavlinskiy said: "I don't think so, although it's 
early yet to speak about this." 

</TEXT>

