<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Does Not Expect Government Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601182994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1630 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] We spoke to Grigoriy Yavlinskiy on the 
telephone today. 
  [Begin recording] [Yavlinskiy] The fact that Yegor Gaydar 
did 
not want to be a decorative figure is quite understandable. 
This confirms the thought that it is not right to use one's 
name to adorn the government. Therefore, I believe, this was 
not a surprise. He has been aware for quite a long time that he 
cannot influence the policy, he still continued to create an 
illusion that these reforms are such and such and that they 
should proceed in such and such a way and that this is indeed 
the government's policy of reforms. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Grigoriy Alekseyevich, if you 
are offered a post in the government, will you agree? 
  [Yavlinskiy] Who exactly will offer it to me? 
  [Unidentified correspondent] The prime minister, probably, 
or 
maybe the president. 
  [Yavlinskiy] I think it is unlikely that the president will 
propose this to me. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] What about the prime minister? 
  [Yavlinskiy] This is of no importance. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Let us say this happened. Would 
you enter the new government or do you also believe that now it 
is impossible to do anything in the government? 
  [Yavlinskiy] I could formulate very many proposals that I 
believe are the necessary prerequisites for the government to be 
able to improve the situation in a limited period of time, let 
us say over a year. These prerequisites include cadre 
reshuffles, the elimination of corruption in the government, a 
clear-cut political policy with regard to reforms, the absence 
of compromises on what has to be done and, first and foremost, 
the acknowledgment of what was done wrong with the aim of 
correcting it. I think that nobody is ready for this. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

