<H3> <TI>   Russia's Choice Officials React to Gaydar Resignation </TI></H3>
<H4>   Faction Coordinator Responds </H4>
<F P=102> LD1601211394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601211394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kirill Ignatyev, the coordinator for the Russia's 
Choice faction in the State Duma, believes that Yegor Gaydar 
will not accept any proposal to return to the government, even 
if the president himself asks him. In an interview with 
Interfax, Ignatyev remarked that Gaydar would not agree to a 
proposal to take any posts in the State Duma. According to the 
faction's coordinator, Gaydar, as its leader, intends to 
concentrate his efforts on organizing the work of the faction, 
and also on creating an apparatus and regional structures for 
the Russia's Choice movement. Ignatyev said that the main aim 
of such work is to prepare for municipal elections scheduled for 
the coming months, in which Russia's Choice plans to achieve 
greater success than during the elections to the State Duma. 

</TEXT>

