<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Choice Officials React to Gaydar Resignation </TI></H3>
<H4>   Member Pochinok Reacts </H4>
<F P=102> LD1701165594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1501 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Member of the Russia's Choice [RC] faction in the 
State Duma Aleksandr Pochinok says Gaydar's statement about his 
stepping down as cabinet member is an indication that although 
he does want to stay where he is to implement his ideas, much of 
the decision making is done behind his back. 
  Gaydar's resignation should not be taken as an attempt to 
bring down the president or his government, Pochinok told 
INTERFAX on Monday. He pledged no opposition to Yeltsin or the 
government on the RC's part, adding that Gaydar was in the mood 
for constructive dialogue. 
  Pochinok sees Gaydar's move as the most honest option, 
saying 
that one must resign if unable to implement his ideas. 
  At the same time, Pochinok, who is a real contender for the 
post of chairman of the planning and budgetary committee, says 
he sees no replacement for Gaydar. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

