<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Response Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701165494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1501 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the LDPR [Liberal 
Democratic Party of Russia] group in the Russian State Duma, 
told Interfax that he was pleased with the decision made by 
Yegor Gaydar not to serve as vice premier in the new government. 
  "Some time ago I told both Boris Yeltsin and Viktor 
Chernomyrdin: `Remove Gaydar, Chubays, Fedorov and Kozyrev and 
you'll have a perfect government,'" Zhirinovskiy emphasized. 
  In his view, Gaydar "must be replaced by a normal 
industrialist." Zhirinovskiy made it plain that his 
parliamentary group was "prepared to endorse any government the 
president wants but I am saying on behalf of my group: `Boris 
Nikolayevich, I implore you to accept Gaydar's resignation.'" 

</TEXT>

