<H3> <TI>   Shokhin Insists on Remaining Deputy Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701134394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1329 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- Russian chief foreign debt 
negotiator Aleksandr Shokhin will agree to remain in the 
government only in case he keeps the post of a deputy prime 
minister. 
  "I may occupy the post of the minister for CIS affairs only 
in case it envisages the status of a vice-premier", Shokhin told 
TASS on Monday. 
  He added that the government is currently facing a 
complicated situation as it has to combine financial 
stabilisation with the policy of promoting production which 
needs enormous finances. 
  The current reorganisation of the government also 
complicates 
the situation, according to Shokhin. 
  "The existing situation in the country calls for two 
necessary things: a strict definition of concrete measures and 
the sharing of roles in the government", he stressed. 

</TEXT>

