<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shmarov: Pact Will End `Isolation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1701094394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0600 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1701094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian Deputy Prime Minister Valeriy Shmarov has 
stated that the tripartite declaration on the elimination of 
nuclear weapons on Ukrainian territory and the accompanying 
appendix, which was just signed in Moscow, is an historic 
document which has laid the foundation for the actual process of 
ending Ukraine's economic and political isolation. In addition, 
the package of documents on denuclearization will enable Ukraine 
to receive international financial aid, including much-needed 
investment to help resolve conversion issues, overcome the 
economic crisis, and provide for the social protection of our 
people. Scientific studies on the dismantling of nuclear 
warheads and their secure withdrawal from Ukrainian territory 
have already been performed. This process will be completed in 
several stages and controlled by appropriate monitoring 
commissions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

