<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Nationalists Reject Nuclear Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701111294 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2219 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 16 Jan -- Delegates to an all-Ukrainian 
conference of the Congress of Ukrainian Nationalists [KUN] 
voiced their attitude toward the signing of a trilateral 
agreement in Moscow on Ukraine's unilateral nuclear disarmament. 
The fact that the president of Ukraine signed this agreement is 
regarded by KUN as being counter to Ukraine's national 
interests. KUN demands that the signed agreement be immediately 
examined and rejected by the Supreme Council of Ukraine, that 
the government be banned from taking any action to prepare for 
its implementation, and that the president of Ukraine be 
impeached and held liable. 
  In its election program, KUN will campaign for a clear-cut 
division of power into legislative, executive, and judicial, for 
a reform of law-enforcement bodies, dissolution of the Security 
Service of Ukraine, and the establishment of effective state 
security services. KUN will campaign for adoption of laws on 
government and public service with a strict system of 
accountability for the actions of state institutions. In the 
economic policy area, KUN will campaign for private ownership, 
giving priority to agriculture and industry. In the foreign 
policy area, KUN stands for Ukraine's cooperation with all 
countries. The Congress [word indistinct] for a non-nuclear 
Ukraine in a non-nuclear world. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
