<H3> <TI>   Results, Reaction to Crimean Elections Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   RPK Deputy Allays Fears </H4>
<F P=102> LD1701230594 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2147 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701230594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, 17 Jan -- A UNIAR correspondent has been 
told by Borys Kyrylov, Crimean Supreme Council people's deputy 
and member of the Coordination Council of the Republican Party 
of Crimea [RPK], that the RPK leader's victory in the elections 
is a surprise for the party. If any, a referendum on the status 
of the peninsula, in Kyrylov's view, will only be of a 
consultative nature and there is no threat to the integrity of 
Ukraine whatsoever. 
  According to that party's decisions and in order to deprive 
the Crimean president of the executive functions of the head of 
government, changes and amendments to the Law on the president 
of the Crimea will be introduced if Yuriy Meshkov scores a 
victory. 

</TEXT>

