<H3> <TI>   Results, Reaction to Crimean Elections Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kravchuk Fires Yermakov </H4>
<F P=102> LD1701150094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1417 GMT 
17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1701150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] There was quite a high turnout in the elections 
for president of the republic on 16 January. [passage omitted] 
  INTERFAX reports that Ivan Yermakov, the Ukrainian 
president's representative in Sevastopol, has been relieved of 
his duties. Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk signed the 
relevant instruction on 17 January. 
  Local observers think this is the Ukrainian leadership's 
first reaction to the results of the presidential elections in 
Crimea, and do not rule out that other actions might follow this 
dismissal. 

</TEXT>

