<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Results, Reaction to Crimean Elections Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Deputy: Elections Unconstitutional </H4>
<F P=102> LD1801111494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
0800 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On Monday [17 January], [Supreme Council Deputy] 
Mykola Porovskyy, committee chairman of the organization Crimea 
With Ukraine, said: I believe the presidential elections in 
Crimea run counter to the Ukrainian constitution. He said that 
the future course of events in Crimea can develop into a 
conflict. It is crucial, he said, to take necessary measures to 
prevent destabilizing processes in Crimea. 
  Two candidates, Yuriy Meshkov and Mykola Bahrov will compete 
against each other in a runoff on 30 January. 

</TEXT>

