<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Communist Party Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401184694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1453 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The ruling body of the Crimean Communist Party made 
public a statement Friday saying that the assassination attempt 
against party leader Leonid Hrach was designed "to frighten the 
presidential candidate" and foil the presidential elections. 
  Shots were fired on January 12 at the windows of Hrach's 
office. One of the party officials was sitting in Hrach's 
armchair at that time. By the latest reports, the bullets 
pierced the table but did not hit the official. 
  The statement expressed its willingness to set up workers' 
self-defense units which would "within the framework of the law 
fight organized crime and stop the Mafia." 
  The Crimean Interior Ministry's press service says, 
meanwhile, that the incident was an act of hooliganism rather 
than an assassination attempt. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

