<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Services Dissolved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701145794 Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service in 
Armenian 1106 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1701145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 17 Jan (ARMENPRES)--By a decree of the 
Republic's president, the operative services of the State 
Directorate for the National Security of the Republic of Armenia 
have been dissolved and the activities of their employees have 
been suspended, with the exception of the Main Directorate for 
the Defense of the State Border and administrative services. 
  The objective is to restructure the inner parts of the State 
Directorate for National Security in light of problems facing 
the State Directorate for National Security under conditions of 
independent statehood. 
  With the same decree, Davit Shahnazaryan--the Armenian 
president's ambassador on special missions--has been appointed 
acting head of the State Directorate for National Security. 
Within three months he must conduct an inspection of the 
quality of the services of the Directorate and draw up and 
submit for the government's approval the bylaws, structure, and 
list of permanent staff. 

</TEXT>

