<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijan Offensive Said Repulsed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701191794 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1701191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation remains tense all along the Karabakh 
battle front. The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic [NKR] Army units 
are waging heavy defensive battles. The NKR Defense Army press 
service has reported that yesterday the Azerbaijani troops 
continued their incessant attacks against the Karabakh 
positions. The fiercest battles took place in the direction of 
Askeran-Agdam. The enemy used scores of armored cars. 
  After destroying one tank, one armored car, and more than 60 
soldiers, the Karabakh fighters forced the Azerbaijanis to 
retreat to their initial positions. Two were killed and seven 
injured on the Armenian side. 
  No substantial changes took place in the other sectors of 
the 
confrontation line. 
  The Karabakh positions at the eastern and southeastern 
sectors of the front have been coming under intensive artillery 
and rocket shelling since this morning. 
  Also, the Azerbaijani Air Force has again become active. A 
number of Azerbaijani warplanes tried to attack Stepanakert, the 
capital of the NKR, between 1000-1200 today. Details are still 
being verified. 
  The Armenian Defense Ministry Press Service has reported 
that 
it has been relatively calm on the Republic's border since 
yesterday night. No serious incidents have been reported. 

</TEXT>

