<H3> <TI>   Premier Receives Iranian Charge d'Affaires </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1401214894 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 2050 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1401214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 2050 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armenian Prime Minister Grant Bagratyan today 
received Iranian Charge d'Affaires in Armenia Ahmad Sobhani. 
They discussed matters pertaining to trade and economic 
cooperation between the two countries, in particular the 
Iran-Armenia gas pipeline, construction of the Megri bridge, 
organization of border trade, road and air transportation, 
coordination of customs activities, and investments. 
  The sides expressed satisfaction at the constructive 
measures 
taken by the governments of the two countries in these fields, 
and noted that there are real opportunities to substantially 
expand the economic ties between Armenia and Iran in 1994. 
  Mutual understanding was displayed on the Karabakh problem. 
They considered unacceptable the use of force which, by further 
deepening the conflict, is preventing the establishment of peace 
in the region. 
  The prime minister highly assessed Iran's efforts for the 
peaceful solution of the problem. 
  Armen Khachaturyan, coordinator of Armenian Government 
affairs, and other officials were present at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

