<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Positive Over Russia's Karabakh Role </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701161794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1542 
GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1701161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan, 17 Jan -- Russia is adhering to an 
impartial stance on the Karabakh settlement and is sincerely 
committed to stopping the bloodshed in the conflict zone, the 
Armenian president's press secretary said here today. Speaking 
at a briefing, Aram Abramyan gave a positive assessment of the 
recent statement by a Russian Foreign Ministry representative on 
Moscow continuing its mission of mediation in the region. 
  The representative of the Armenian leadership reported on 
the 
continuation of diplomatic efforts to overcome the crisis in the 
region, in particular, the continuing visit to the region by 
Vladimir Kazimirov, the Russian president's special envoy. The 
press secretary reiterated the known fact that Yerevan and 
Stepanakert have responded positively to the new peace-making 
initiative by Russia and the CSCE. Now it is up to Azerbaijan, 
noted the Armenian representative. 

</TEXT>

