<H3> <TI>   Intellectuals Invite Zhirinovskiy for Jan Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1401141094 Moscow KURANTY in Russian 14 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> MK1401141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KURANTY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Konstantin Petrosov: "Will Zhirinovskiy Visit </F>
Armenia?"] 
  [Text] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Liberal 
Democratic Party of Russia, will visit the republic in 
mid-January at the invitation of Armenia's Council of 
Intellectuals, according to local mass media reports. 
  It is hard to say whether the fact is trustworthy and 
whether 
Vladimir Volfovich's coming to Armenia in the near future is 
possible at all especially in the wake of his promise to turn 
independent Armenia into a Yerevan gubernia as part of a Russian 
empire. 
  Armenian social scientists, however, think Armenia does have 
a social base for forces like Zhirinovskiy's, because populism 
and socialist ideas take a far from back seat in semi-starving 
countries. 

</TEXT>

