<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   New National Security Committee Chairman Named </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1801092294 Tallinn BNS in English 1828 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1801092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Vilnius, Jan 17, BNS -- MP Vytautas Petkevicius, 
member of the ruling Lithuanian Democratic Labor Party [LDDP], 
was approved as the new chairman of the parliament's National 
Security Committee Monday. 
  Petkevicius was supported by all seven committee members 
present at the meeting. Five other committee members, all 
representatives of the rightist opposition, were not present. 
  The new chairman said he will resign immediately if work 
does 
not go smooth in the new post. Petkevicius said his primary aim 
is to deal with the critical situation in the armed forces. 82 
deaths were reported in the Voluntary State Defense Service over 
the past two years. Legal action in the state defense system was 
taken 162 times for the loss of weapons, assaults and other 
criminal offenses. 
  Petkevicius was elected in accordance with the parliament's 
resolution saying that the post would belong to the ruling LDDP 
faction. But neither Petkevicius, not three other members of the 
committee, have registered themselves on the LDDP faction after 
the new faction registration rules came into effect. 
  Petkevicius was the acting chairman of the committee for 
several months after the resignation of MP Gediminas Kirkilas. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

