<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Intensive' Mortar Attack on Afghan Border Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601073394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0653 
GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601073394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 16 Jan--An ITAR-TASS correspondent at the 
headquarters of the command of the Russian border troops in 
Tajikistan was informed today that one of the border posts of 
the Gandyshskiy border detachment came under intensive mortar 
fire yesterday evening. 
  More than 20 mortars were launched along the stretch of the 
border with Afghanistan, some of which exploded right in the 
outskirts of the Ayvadzh border settlement. Russian border 
guards neutralized the enemy's weapon emplacements with powerful 
artillery fire. There were no casualties among border guards 
and local civilians. 
  On the same day, Tajik opposition fighters fired from the 
territory of Afghanistan at a sector controlled by border guards 
from the Moskovskiy border unit. The Russian border guards 
neutralized the firing points of the mojahedin with answering 
fire. 

</TEXT>

