<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dushanbe January 17 TIA-KHOVAR-TASS -- At least ten 
armed transgressors were killed in a clash on the Tajik-Afghan 
border this past Sunday when an armed anti-government group of 
more than twenty militants attempted to cross the border from 
Afghanistan into Tajikistan. 
  An Uzbek battalion of the CIS collective peacekeeping force 
helped the Russian borderguards repel the transgressors who 
retreated to Afghanistan. 
  None of the CIS and Russian servicemen was hurt. 

