<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Receives Over 99 Percent </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601092294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0715 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The final results have been compiled for the 15 
January nationwide referendum in Turkmenistan. Live on the air, 
here is our Ashgabat correspondent, Merdyen Amanov: 
  [Amanov] I think that Mayak listeners will be interested to 
hear the results of the nationwide referendum held yesterday on 
whether to extend the tenure of office of Saparmurad Niyazov for 
a second five-year term. Literally an hour ago the Central 
Electoral Commission completed its work and Turkmenistan will 
not now be holding its next presidential elections. 
  The final results of the referendum are as follows: The 
number of people who received voting slips was 1,959,637. 
Turnout was 99.99 percent of the electorate, and 99.99 percent 
of those who voted were in favor of extending the term in office 
of President Niyazov. The vote against was 212 people, which 
comes to 0.01 percent. 

</TEXT>

