<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Chernomyrdin Discuss Composition of Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801101594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0920 
GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Ivan Ivanov and Gennadiy </F>
Talalayev] 
  [Excerpts] Moscow, 18 Jan -- A meeting between Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin and Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin 
began in the Kremlin at midday [0900 GMT]. This is one of the 
regular Tuesday meetings. They are expected to discuss a draft 
presidential decree on the new composition of the Russian 
government. [passage omitted] 
  ITAR-TASS correspondents have learned from trustworthy 
sources that the meeting between the president and the prime 
minister will continue until 1400 hours [1100 GMT] and that 
Boris Yeltsin will today give final confirmation to the 
government line-up. 

</TEXT>

