<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Troops To Fire To Protect `Military Objects' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401155094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1529 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Kuchina] </F>
  [Text] Riga January 14 TASS -- The command of the Russian 
North-Western troops ordered Russian military in Latvia to open 
fire in case of new attacks on military objects, the 
north-western troops press-centre reported Friday. 
  Officers sent to settle conflict situation are to be 
accompanied by armed guards. Armed units on duty will protect 
military objects which do not have permanent guards. In order 
to avoid misunderstanding commanders of military units are to 
notify local authorities and residents about these measures. 
  The order was issued in connection with the incident, which 
took place in Latvia Monday, when four military objects were 
blockaded and two generals were arrested and delivered in 
manacles to the state border. 
  These actions "cast doubt on promises of Latvia about its 
intention to solve all the problems of Russian troops in Latvia 
in a civilized way, the ability of the Latvian state to control 
activities of local troops under their command", 

</TEXT>

