<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ulmanis Views Order as `Provocative' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701185594 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1801 GMT 17 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1701185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis views as 
provocative, an order issued by the command of the Northwestern 
Group of Russian Forces last week. The order allows the use of 
arms in case of attacks on, or other illegal actions toward 
Russian military personnel or military facilities. Ulmanis told 
a news conference this today, adding that such an action by the 
Russian side is not acceptable for him as president. Ulmanis 
believes that this step on the part of the command of the 
Northwestern Group of Forces is not a very correct reply to 
Ulmanis' correct action during the provocation of 10 January 
[when two Russian generals were detained by Latvians in Riga]. 
  As Igor Golin, the head of the press center of the 
Northwestern Group of Forces told the Baltic News Agency, the 
above-mentioned order will not be applicable in cases when 
Latvian border guards detain Russian military personnel who try 
to enter Latvia without the necessary documents. According to 
Golin, the order allows a person who guards a Russian military 
facility located in Latvia to use arms in case of an attack 
after a verbal warning or warning shot in the air, as it is 
provided by the Russian military rules. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

