<H3> <TI>   U.S.-Belarusian Documents Signed Before Clinton Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401175594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1650 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1401175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Lyushkevich] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 14 Jan -- Within the framework of U.S. 
President Bill Clinton's upcoming visit to the republic, a 
number of Belarusian-U.S. agreements was signed at the 
Belarusian Foreign Ministry today. The agreements were signed 
by Foreign Minister Petr Kravchenko, and David Swartz, the U.S. 
ambassador to Belarus. 
  The signed documents include an agreement between the United 
States and Belarusian Governments on scientific and technical 
cooperation, exchange letters to the treaty between the Republic 
of Belarus and the United States on encouraging and mutually 
protecting investments, a general agreement on promoting 
projects between the Finance Ministry and the National Bank of 
the Republic of Belarus and the U.S. Export-Import Bank, as well 
as a memorandum on mutual understanding between the U.S. 
Government and the government of the Republic of Belarus 
regarding the intent to sign an agreement on setting up a joint 
commission for agro-business and rural development. 
  Also, the Belarusian Foreign Ministry and the U.S. Embassy 
exchanged notes on the Republic of Belarus' application of the 
Soviet-U.S. agreement on cooperation between customs. 

</TEXT>

