<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich on Gaydar Remarks on Monetary Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601231294 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 2200 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601231294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Yegor Gaydar said that one of the reasons for his 
resignation was the inter-bank agreement on unification of the 
monetary systems of Russia and Belarus. Concerning this, 
Stanislav Shushkevich, head of the Belarusian Parliament, 
expressed to INTERFAX the supposition that Gaydar had not been 
presented with an analysis of Belarus's expenditure on 
elimination of the aftermath of the Chernobyl accident, on which 
the republic annually spends 15 percent of its annual budget. 
  Minsk believes that Russia should take into consideration 
the 
factor of the Chernobyl tragedy in the talks on creating a 
monetary union with Belarus. 

</TEXT>

