<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Mkhedrioni' Paramilitary Group Disarms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401175794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1453 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Most members of the Georgian paramilitary group, 
formerly known as "Mkhedrioni," have surrendered arms as of 
Friday, Interfax was told by the group's spokesman. Those who 
are against will be excluded from the group, he said. 
  The decision for disarmament of the group headed by the 
founder of "Mkhedrioni," Djaba Ioseliani, was made January 10 by 
the Georgian authorities to help restore order in the republic. 
The surrendered arms are stored in the group's warehouses. 

</TEXT>

