<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Sends APCs to Downtown Tbilisi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1501192794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1704 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1501192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Albert Kochetkov] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi January 15 TASS -- The Georgian Interior 
Ministry introduced today APCs in key areas of downtown Tbilisi 
and concentrated there almost all personnel of the city police 
due to Zviadist attempts to hold mourning arrangements in 
connection with the supposed death of the ex-president. 
  Although the death has not been confirmed it is believed the 
body of Zviad Gamsakhurdia is buried in western Georgia. 
Zviadists demand a funeral ceremony: a minute of silence with 
the suspension of work of enterprises, organizations and 
traffic, as well as rallies that are banned by the state of 
emergency regime introduced in Georgia on September 20, 1993. 
  No excesses or clashes between the Tbilisi police and 
supporters of the ex-president were reported today. 

</TEXT>

