<H3> <TI>   Appeals for Burial Help </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701171094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1630 GMT 
17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1701171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Manana, Zviad Gamsakhurdia's widow, has sent a 
telegram to Russian President Boris Yeltsin and the Russian 
Federal Assembly asking for help in having her husband's body 
buried in Chechnya. She informed the Chechenpress agency about 
this today. 
  The widow of Georgia's former president, who committed 
suicide, said she was categorically against representatives of 
Tbilisi officialdom carrying out forensic tests on her husband's 
body. Her view is that they would be used for political 
purposes by Zviad Gamsakhurdia's enemies. 

</TEXT>

