<H3> <TI>   Edict Changes National Security Agency Structure </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801204894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1835 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Presidential Bulletin" feature: No. 11 (501)] </F>
  [Text] President Levon Ter-Petrosyan has signed a decree 
changing the command structure of the National Security Agency, 
dissolving the operative services and suspending the activities 
of its personnel other than the border guards and technical, 
financial and other services. 
  Davil Shakhnazaryan, 38, Armenian parliament deputy who was 
presidential special envoy, has been appointed acting agency 
chief replacing Eduard Simonyan. 
  Shakhnazaryan has three months to screen the agency 
personnel 
and draft the charter, structure and personnel requirements for 
government approval. 
  Aram Abramyan, the president's spokesman, told Interfax that 
the National Security Agency needed an overhaul to deal with the 
challenges facing an independent state. 

</TEXT>

