<H3> <TI>   U.S. Allegedly Offers To Buy Fuel From Baku </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1801135194 Yerevan SNARK in English 0946 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1801135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, January 18 (SNARK)--The trustworthy sources 
told SNARK the USA official representative offers to solve the 
humanitarian kerosene deliveries problem by purchasing the fuel 
from Azerbaijan. 
  It's known the great amount of kerosene is in the Batumi 
port 
and it's impossible to deliver it to Armenia because of the 
situation at the Georgian roads. 
  So, Azerbaijan has an additional chance to earn using the 
situation. 
  According to the data SNARK News Agency possesses, the price 
for the Azerbaijani kerosene is in 1.5 times more than the price 
for the fuel which could be brought by planes from Russia and in 
2 times more than the Irani kerosene price. Azerbaijani could 
use the acquired currency to go on with the military actions in 
Karabakh, so, can this way be considered as the accepted one. 
Besides, such deliveries are the violations of the "Freedom 
Defense Law", accepted by the USA Congress which prohibits the 
USA Government to finance Azerbaijan because of the blockade 
course he accepted in respect to Armenia and Karabakh. 

</TEXT>

