<F P=103> LD1801213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In connection with the statements by Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev on a change in Russian foreign policy 
relating to the CIS states and the Baltic region, Latvian 
Council of Ministers President Valdis Birkavs has commented as 
follows: 
  [begin Birkavs recording] Mr. Kozyrev has announced that the 
CIS and the Baltic countries [words indistinct] regions in which 
quite important Russian interests are concentrated, and from 
which the main threat to these interests [words indistinct]; 
speaking of the military presence in this region, complete 
withdrawal from this region, that is, the (?complete lack) of 
military presence in this region is extremely [word indistinct]. 
There is no need to withdraw from those regions which for 
centuries have been in the Russian sphere of interest, and there 
is no need to be afraid of these words. A security vacuum will 
start to form if Russia's troops are withdrawn from here. 
Rather than fleeing, supplementary forces are being brought in, 
which are always threatening, in some cases hostile to Russia. 
  In my opinion, this announcement in fact indicates a serious 
change in Russia's position. Moreover, I cannot but associate 
this position with the recent meeting of U.S. and Russian 
leaders. Latvia must, therefore, absolutely reinforce its 
position, and in my view security policy has become a state 
priority [words indistinct]. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

