<F P=102>  LD1801211594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1805 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801211594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Presidential Bulletin" No. 11 feature] </F>
  [Text] President Guntis Ulmanis, at the briefing Monday, 
said that he regrets Yegor Gaydar's resignation, since he 
believes that Gaydar's economic policies are rational and 
concrete. 
  Latvia's Prime Minister Valdis Birkavs believes that Yegor 
Gaydar's resignation will not influence Russian-Latvian economic 
relations. 
  He told Interfax that over the past two years the volume of 
economic contacts between the two countries had decreased so 
much that it would not be serious to talk about any further 
deterioration. 
  He believes that whenever possible the Latvian government 
will continue economic dialogue with the Russian government 
irrespective of the changes in it. 
  He described Gaydar's resignation as "Russia's inner 
political games" which will have no decisive impact on the 
neighboring states." 

</TEXT>

