<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accident at Atomic Plant of `Local' Significance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1801144094 Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA in Ukrainian 15 Jan 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU1801144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by the DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA News Service: </F>
"Zaporizhzhya: An Accident at the Atomic Electric Power 
Station"] 
  [Text] As reported by the Information Center of the 
Zaporizhzhya Atomic Electric Power Station [AES], on 12 January 
at 1000 [local time], [radioactive] contamination was revealed 
in a compressed-air pipeline in one of the auxiliary 
technological buildings. No contamination of the plant's 
territory, irradiation of the personnel, or discharges into the 
environment took place. There is no danger either for the 
population or for people working at the plant. 
  It has been tentatively found that radioactive water entered 
the compressed-air pipeline from the fourth power unit due to 
the lack of tightness in one of the locking valves in the 
compressed-air line, which is used for processing the 
ion-exchange resins in filters of the special water-purification 
installation. 
  Work on decontaminating the compressed-air pipeline has 
already been completed. Therefore, the incident was local in 
character and had no effect upon the plant's operation. 
  A commission is investigating the causes of the accident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

