<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Lauds Arrest of January Coup Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1801163294 Tallinn BNS in English 1050 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1801163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 18, BNS -- Lithuanian President 
Algirdas Brazauskas said he is greatly satisfied with the arrest 
of Mykolas Burokevicius and Juozas Jarmalavicius, the believed 
organizers of a failed coup attempt in Lithuania in January 1991. 
  The two were detained in Minsk Saturday [15 January]. 
Brazauskas expressed gratitude to the Belarussian Government and 
special services for extraditing the alleged state criminals who 
are accused of high treason and complicity in aggravated murder. 
As a result of a military aggression in Vilnius Jan. 13, 1991, 
13 civilians were killed and around 700 injured. 
  The Lithuanian president expressed hope that the 
investigation of the January 13th case will be fast and smooth 
and that "justice will finally be restored." 

</TEXT>

