<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seimas Rejects President's Veto on Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801223994 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in International Service 
in Lithuanian 2200 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801223994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> International </F>Language: &lt;f 105&gt; Lithuanian 
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Lithuanian Seimas has rejected the president's 
veto on a law devoted to improvements in agriculture. Today, 
the Seimas endorsed the law passed in December. This document 
was returned by President Brazauskas to the Seimas to 
reconsider. It was stated in his decree that some norms of the 
law did not correspond with the principle of establishing market 
economy. The government diktat, legalized by this law, to all 
agricultural producers, irrespective of the form of their 
ownership, was the most unsuitable to the president. The law, 
among other things, provides for quotas of the purchase of 
agricultural products, fixed by the government, to all 
enterprises processing agricultural products. 
  According to the constitution, the law repeatedly passed by 
the Seimas, must be signed by the president within three days 
and announced without delay. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

