<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich Views Monetary Union With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801172594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1454 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The head of the Belarusian parliament, Stanislav 
Shushkevich, thinks that the joining of Belarusian and Russian 
monetary systems should not be viewed as the solution to all 
difficulties. "Our economy should be reformed by ourselves, not 
by Russia," he declared in a televised statement Monday evening. 
  Nevertheless, Shushkevich conceded that a monetary union 
with 
Russia is capable of considerably improving the economic 
situation in Belarus. 
  According to him, to ensure normal working of the proposed 
monetary union it is necessary to fix equal prices for fuel and 
basic raw materials and establish a customs union between 
Belarus and Russia. 
  With reference to the possibility of his resignation during 
the current parliamentary session, Shushkevich said he is aware 
that a group of deputies intended to "raise this issue." He 
would resign on his own, if he believed that the next speaker 
will induce legislators to fix a date for early parliamentary 
elections, Shushkevich said. 

</TEXT>

