<H3> <TI>   Views Political, Economic Problems </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801194694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1247 
GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM correspondent Valentina Menshikova] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 18 Jan (TASS) -- "I hope that Yegor Gaydar's 
resignation will not affect relations with Russia," Belarus 
Supreme Soviet Chairman Stanislav Shushevich stated in the 
evening of 17 January in a live broadcast of Belarusian 
television, replying to viewers' questions. 
  He described the situation in Belarus as complicated and 
contradictory, having noted that it should be fundamentally 
changed and that this can be done only through a new composition 
of parliament by early elections, which he is advocating. 
  Having touched on a possible monetary merger with Russia, 
the 
Supreme Soviet chairman stated that if the merger of monetary 
systems produces merely a parity of prices for fuel, one could 
hope for an improvement of the economic situation. "However, no 
one will establish order in our house for us. It is for us to 
decide how we are going to go on living," he stressed. 

</TEXT>

