<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Communique Reported 17 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701204094 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 17 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1701204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of Azerbaijani Defense Ministry communique issued on </F>
17 January; read by announcer] 
  [Text] The Armenian military units launched an attack 
against the Fizuli sector of the front line at 0100 today. 
Azerbaijan's military forces counterattacked and forced the 
enemy units to retreat to their positions, after suffering 
several casualties. 
  According to the information received from the occupied 
areas, the Armenian military command has involved the militia 
units in the fighting to achieve its occupationist objectives in 
Khankendi [formerly Stepanakert] and the other occupied areas in 
Azerbaijan. 
  Meanwhile, helicopters continue to urgently transfer 
reinforcements and military equipment from Armenia to Daghlyk 
Karabakh. They transfer the wounded Armenians back to Armenia 
after unloading their cargo. The dead bodies of Armenian 
conscripts from Armenia are transferred in trucks from Daghlyk 
Karabakh to that Republic through the Lachin corridor every day. 
  More than 1,000 enemy troops have been killed in the recent 
clashes. That has been concealed from the Armenian people. It 
seems that the dissemination of such reports will not be in the 
interest of Armenia's leading circles and those who wage the 
bloody war. 

</TEXT>

