<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Heavy Losses on Both Sides </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601193294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1743 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1601193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At about 7:30, January 16, following an intensive 
artillery preparation, the Azerbaijani troops assumed an 
offensive in two directions -- the Matagis-Akop and Kamari 
section in the Mardakert Region, and the Askeran-Agdam 
direction, informed sources in Stepanakert told Interfax. 
  By 10:00, the Azerbaijani attacks were rebuffed by Karabakh 
forces in the Northern direction. One Azerbaijani tank was 
destroyed and 30 Azerbaijani soldiers were killed. The 
Azerbaijani army had to retreat to the earlier assumed positions. 
  By midday, heavy fighting continued at the eastern limits of 
Nagorno-Karabakh. Both sides are sustaining losses. Local 
fighting continues in the other sections of the front. 
  The Azerbaijani Defense Ministry announced, meanwhile, that 
on Sunday morning, well-equipped Armenian units assumed an 
offensive in the Fizuli Region, moving towards the Iranian 
border. Attacks are being made on the villages of Goradiz and 
Derdchinar. 
  During fierce combat operations the Azerbaijani army 
rebuffed 
the Armenian attack, throwing Armenian units back to the initial 
positions. A source in the Azerbaijani Defense Ministry 
announced that two Armenian tanks, one armored vehicle and 1 
artillery piece had been destroyed. Armenians suffered great 
losses. 
  The same source reports, that in December and January, more 
than a thousand Armenian soldiers were killed or wounded. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

