<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Intensive Shelling' Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701131294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1248 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701131294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Barykin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- The intensive shelling of 
Nagorno-Karabakh positions began today in the morning by the 
Azeri National Army at the eastern and south-eastern sections of 
the Nagorno-Karabakh front. According to the press service of 
the headquarters of the Nagorno-Karabakh Defence Army, units of 
the Nagorno-Karabakh Army are fighting defence battles along the 
whole of the front line. 
  At 10.00 in the morning Azeri assault planes made five 
attempts to bomb Stepanakert, a spokesman for the 
Nagorno-Karabakh press and information department told ITAR-TASS 
by telephone. However, anti-aircraft defence units made them 
retreat. The population is being warned in time about the 
coming air raids. 
  According to the press service of the defence army 
headquarters, the fighting was especially fierce at the eastern 
and Askeran-Agdam sections. Dozens of Azeri armoured vehicles 
took part in it. The Nagorno-Karabakh troops destroyed a tank, 
an armoured personnel carrier and killed 60 enemy soldiers, 
forcing the Azeri troops to retreat to their initial positions. 
In the Nagorno-Karabakh units two men were killed and seven 
wounded. 

</TEXT>

