<H3> <TI>   Meeting With Armenian President Uncertain </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701222094 Baku TURAN in English 1656 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1701222094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 15 (Turan)--As a reliable source at 
Azerbaijani President's staff told TURAN news agency, a supposed 
meeting of Azerbaijani and Armenian presidents is being worked 
out. Russian capital Moscow is the most prominent place for this 
meeting. Azerbaijan's ambassador to Russia Ramiz Rizayev also 
did not excluded the possibility of the meeting. 
  Meanwhile, Azerbaijan's Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov told 
the press in Baku recently, that "Armenian party's approach to 
this meeting is of a non-constructive character". 
  To his mind, serious documents have to be prepared to be 
signed by the end of the meeting. Gasanov said that the 
Armenian side neither proposes such documents, nor accepts 
Azerbaijan's proposals. 
  Touching upon the recent interview of Robert Kocharyan, the 
leader of Armenian community of Nagorno-Karabakh to the Russian 
TV, Gasanov said, that "this interview again proved that the 
Republic of Armenia arms Nagorno-Karabakh separatist fighters. 
It has become clear, that Armenian side tries to solve the 
conflict by all means forcibly". 
  Such position, Mr. Gasanov considers, cannot be the basis 
for 
the negotiation process on regulation of the conflict. 

</TEXT>

