<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Peace Plan Draws Mixed Reaction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1401122094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 14 Jan 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK1401122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aydyn Mekhtiyev: "Baku Not Yet Ready To Accept </F>
Russia's Plan for Karabakh Problem Settlement, but the 
Document's Main Provisions Have Already Been Determined"] 
  [Text] The talks of Azerbaijani authorities with Vladimir 
Kazimirov, special representative of the Russian Federation 
president, that ended 12 January in Baku, were held in a 
constructive atmosphere and enabled the sides to agree on the 
main principles of a peaceful solution to the Karabakh problem. 
This is what Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov said in 
an interview for NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA. He emphasized that the 
draft agreement on the peaceful settlement proposed by the 
Russian diplomat drew a mixed reaction from the Baku 
authorities. According to the Azerbaijani minister, the draft 
does not include provisions on the immediate and unconditional 
withdrawal of Armenian troops from all occupied territories, on 
which Baku has been insisting. Instead, the two sides were 
invited to sit down at a negotiating table to discuss all 
contentious matters. Gasan Gasanov asked the Russian diplomat 
to make substantial adjustments to the peaceful settlement 
draft. "Azerbaijan insists on a phased solution to the 
question," he told your NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA correspondent. "We 
will give security guarantees to the Armenian population of 
Nagorno-Karabakh, but in exchange the Armenian side must create 
all requisite conditions for a return of more than a million 
Azerbaijani refugees to the areas of their permanent residence." 
When asked by the NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA correspondent about 
Baku's attitude to Moscow's proposal for the Iranian-Azerbaijani 
border to be protected jointly, the Azerbaijani minister said: 
"This proposal may be a matter of discussion after Azerbaijan 
and Iran sign a treaty "On the Regime of the Azerbaijani-Iranian 
Border." During my visit to Tehran we reached agreement on 
setting up a working group for drawing up this document." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-56629 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov012_r_94011" </HT>


