<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev's Meeting With UN Representative Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701204194 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 17 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1701204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Geydar Aliyev received Mahmud al-Sa'id, UN 
representative in Azerbaijan, on 17 January. Aliyev briefed his 
guest on the serious situation in the Republic and Azerbaijan's 
recent gains on the front lines. Stressing that Azerbaijan's 
troops control Fizulinskiy, Agdamskiy, Agderinskiy, and 
Kelbadzharskiy Rayons, Aliyev noted that the world has to be 
accurately informed on the situation in Azerbaijan. He also 
recalled his meeting with President Levon Ter-Petrosyan in 
Ashgabat and stressed that he wishes to find a peaceful solution 
to the dispute. 
  President Aliyev said: We want to find a peaceful way to 
retrieve our territory. However, we shall not allow Armenia's 
occupationist forces to continue to tread on even an inch of 
Azerbaijan's territory. 
  Later, Aliyev thanked al-Sa'id for the UN aid to 
Azerbaijan's 
refugees and said that he appreciated his visit to the front 
lines to meet with the refugees. 
  Mahmud al-Sa'id said that the UN organization plans to 
maintain its humanitarian aid to Azerbaijan in 1994. He also 
said that UN aid will be maintained until the dispute is 
resolved. 
  State Adviser Vefa Gulizade attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

