<H3> <TI>   Russian Peacekeeping Force for Abkhaz Conflict </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801184594 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in 
Georgian 1700 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi First Program Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Gennadiy Dolgachev, head of the press center of the 
Russian troops in Georgia, has said that units of the Russian 
army in Transcaucasia will be used as a peace-keeping force in 
the zone of the Georgian-Abkhaz conflict. He said that 
everything is ready to start this measure. 
  The agreement to deploy a peace-keeping force in the 
conflict 
zone was reached at talks between Georgian and Abkhaz 
delegations in Geneva. This force will supervise the return of 
the refugees to Abkhazia, whose number, as you know, exceeds 
200,000. The return of the refugees is due to start on 10 
February. 

</TEXT>

