<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Appraises Government `Negatively' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801130694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1148 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Eduard Shevardnadze has assessed the performance of 
Georgia's government led by Otar Patsatsia extremely negatively. 
As INTERFAX learned from well-informed sources in Tbilisi, he 
criticized the Cabinet on Monday at a session held by the 
parliamentary majority behind closed doors. The parliamentary 
majority had been formed by Shevardnadze's supporters to ensure 
more coordinated backing for his reforms. 
  Addressing the session, Shevardnadze expressed 
dissatisfaction with the work of some ministers, and even raised 
the issue of forming a new government. 

</TEXT>

