<H3> <TI>   Security Minister on Gamsakhurdia's Exhumation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801113094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Georgian authorities know where former Georgian 
President Zviad Gamsakhurdia, who committed suicide in a village 
in Western Georgia in the early hours of 1 January, is buried. 
  INTERFAX reports this was stated by Igor Giorgadze, the 
Georgian minister of security, at a news conference in Tbilisi 
yesterday evening. 
  He said that a group of specialists from Russia, Germany, 
and 
the United States was due to depart for Western Georgia today to 
exhume and inspect Gamsakhurdia's body. 
  Only a visual inspection will be carried out, in keeping 
with 
what was requested by the former President's family. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

