<H3> <TI>   Deputy Chairman on Federation Council's Independence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401232494 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1800 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1401232494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] [Correspondent Vladimir 
Perfilyev] The press is starting to say that this chamber [the 
Federation Council] may become tame and end up in the 
president's pocket. Are you not apprehensive about that 
possibility? 
  [Valeryan Viktorov, Federation Council deputy chairman] Oh 
no, I am not apprehensive. You must have noticed that we have 
very independently-minded people sitting in this hall, and I 
believe it would be difficult to put them in someone's pocket. 
For instance, the head of our chamber is Vladimir Filippovich 
Shumeyko, who is also a very independent person. He will not 
blindly follow instructions, be it from the president or from 
the head of our government, but on the other hand I am 
absolutely convinced that he will not enter into unnecessary 
confrontation between the president and the government. 

</TEXT>

