<H3> <TI>   New Deputy Speaker Calls To Defend Federation's Regions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801070194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0640 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801070194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valentina Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Cheboksary, January 18 (TASS) -- The newly elected 
deputy speaker of the Federation Council of the Russian 
Parliament, Velerian Viktorov, former head of the government of 
Chuvashia, said in an interview with ITAR-TASS that he intends 
to defend the interests of Russian regions. 
  He pointed out that it is necessary to pay attention to 
equal 
development of all regions of the Russian Federation, and 
primarily, to the creation of a legal basis adequate to economic 
reform to enable it to go ahead. Viktorov is against radical 
changes and welcomes an evolutional development of society. 
  According to preliminary reports, Viktorov will be in 
charge of economic issues in the upper chamber of the Russian 
Parliament. He came out in support of principally new relations 
expected to be established between the centre and the subjects 
of the federation in the second quarter of 1994 when regions 
begin to contribute a definite amount to the federal budget, 
spending the remaining funds on their own needs. 

</TEXT>

