<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Travkin Calls For Duma To Stabilize Society </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401154094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1512 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- The potential for 
self-organisation of the State Duma is much higher than that of 
the previous parliament. The Duma has already shown 
effectiveness by electing speaker, Nikolay Travkin, leader of 
the Democratic Party of Russia, said at a news conference on 
Friday. 
  Travkin believes the Duma can have a stabilising effect on 
society. 
  He said his party has not entered and is not going to enter 
any blocs, but members of the Democratic Party would be 
gratified if their interests coincide with those of other 
factions. 
  Travkin said the Democratic Party objects to possible 
construction of a new parliament building, believing that this 
would only discredit the new legistative body. 
  He added that a regular congress of the Democratic Party of 
Russia will be held on February 18-19. He said the purpose of 
the congress is to make the party less amorphous and impart to 
it a more rigid structure. 

</TEXT>

