<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   LDPR To Seek Foreign Affairs Committee Head for Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401205994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1911 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The LDP [Liberal Democratic Party] will battle for 
the post of head of the Foreign Relations Committee to be given 
to its leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, Deputy party Chairman 
Stanislav Zhebrovskiy told Interfax. 
  In the meantime, Speaker-Elect of the State Duma Ivan Rybkin 
speaking late on Friday [14 January] described Vice Premier 
Aleksandr Shokhin as the only candidate professionally fit to 
take the post. Shokhin belongs to the Party of Russian Unity 
and Concord. 
  At the same time, the Speaker called for committees to be 
formed on a proportional basis so that none of the factions 
remained unrepresented. 
  The Russia's Choice Party [RC] will not allow extremists 
from 
the Zhirinovskiy-led faction to take control of the key 
committees, and above all, the foreign relations committee, RC 
spokesman Kirill Ignatyev told Interfax. He said Zhirinovskiy's 
chairmanship of the committee would mean instability and 
probably war to Russia. 
  The faction will stick to its position in talks with other 
groups, Ignatyev said. Leaders of the parliamentary factions 
and Rybkin-led New Regional Policy group are due to meet at 
14:00 on Saturday to discuss the sharing of committees among 
them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

