<H3> <TI>   State Duma Announces Recess Until 17 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401174394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1610 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1401174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 14 Jan -- Deputies in the State Duma have 
adopted a decision to hold a recess in the sessions of the lower 
chamber of the Federal Assembly until 17 January. 
  Opening the evening session, Ivan Rybkin, the elected 
chairman of the State Duma, said that he believed the Duma's 
main task was "to finish structuring itself and begin lawmaking 
work." 
  Boris Zolotukhin, who spoke next, informed the people's 
deputies of a coordinated decision by leaders of deputies' 
associations to hold a recess in the plenary sessions of the 
Duma to allow for the work of factions and deputies' groups. 
During the recess "the nominations for and the number of Duma 
deputy chairmen are to be agreed upon, as well as the 
nominations for the posts of heads of State Duma committees." 
  The composition of the Duma Credentials Commission was also 
approved before the recess. The commission must now elect its 
own head. 

</TEXT>

