<H3> <TI>   State Duma Continues Work 17 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701091294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0802 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- The State Duma will 
continue its work today. Its session will begin at 14.00. The 
lower chamber of the Russian parliament is expected to discuss 
issues dealing with the election of deputy chairmen of the Duma 
and heads of parliamentary committees. 
  Last Saturday those issues were tentatively discussed at a 
conference of chairman of the State Duma Ivan Rybkin and heads 
of parliamentary groups, held behind closed doors. 
  The planned number of deputy chairmen and the names of 
candidates to those posts remain a secret. The names of 
candidates to the posts of heads of parliamentary committees 
(there are going to be 18 of them) are not known either. 
  In the opinion of observers, the main struggle will develop 
over the posts of heads of the committees on international 
affairs, defence and security. 

</TEXT>

