<H3> <TI>   LDPR Will Not Receive Key Positions on Duma Commissions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701125994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1245 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- The Liberal Democratic 
Party [LDPR] of nationalist leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy will 
not get key positions in the State Duma and Zhirinovskiy himself 
will not head the Foreign Affairs Commission which he planned to 
do, according to Kirill Ignatyev, a member of the Russia's 
Choice bloc. 
  He told reporters on Monday [17 January] that all factions, 
including the LDPR, had agreed that Zhirinovsly's people will 
not head the commissions on foreign affairs, on defence and 
security, on federation affairs and the budget. 
  In response Zhirinovskiy proposed to create a special 
commission for him which would deal with geopolitical issues, 
according to Ignatyev. 
  "We could not react to it in any other way than with 
sarcasm", he added. 

</TEXT>

