<H3> <TI>   Kept Off Chairmen List </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1701173094 Paris AFP in English 1716 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1701173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, Jan 17 (AFP) -- Communists and reformers of 
the Yabloko coalition will dominate key Russian parliamentary 
committees after a vote in the Duma on Monday [17 January] 
sidelined ultra-nationalists into less important technical 
groups. 
  Right-wing firebrand Vladimir Zhirinovsky was kept off the 
list of chairmen while one of his supporters was elected to head 
a specially established commission on geopolitical affairs. 
  The deputies approved by 290 to 63 votes with eight 
abstentions a package of positions that gave the key 
legislative, security, social and religious commissions to 
communists. 
  Reformists were elected to the vital budget and foreign 
affairs commissions while Zhirinovsky's Liberal Democratic Party 
took the commission for industry, transport energy and public 
works and a group that will look into natural resources. 

</TEXT>

