<H3> <TI>   Value of Votes in Duma To Depend on Deputies' Rank </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701105294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1007 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- Heads of factions of the 
Russian State Duma decided at their session today that each vote 
cast in the Duma will be assessed in points. A vote cast by the 
speaker will be estimated at five points, first deputy speaker - 
four points, a committee chairman - one point, a deputy 
committee chairman - 0.5 points. During vote-counting, every 
point will be considered equal to 7 deputies' votes. 
  The "Russia's Choice" bloc which received 11 points in the 
Duma council will have the best advantages. It is followed by 
the "New Regional Policy" faction which collected 9.5 points, 
the faction of the Liberal Democratic Party (9 points), the 
Agrarian Party (8 points) and other factions in hierarchy 
depending on the number of points they collected. 
  The council of the State Duma will consist of 15 members, 
including the speaker and deputy speakers, heads of factions and 
deputy groups, committees, chairmen of vote-counting and 
mandatory commissions and a human rights commissioner. 
  The "weightlifting categories" of factions and parliamentary 
groups are expected to play a decisive role when adopting draft 
bills. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

