<H3> <TI>   Lower House To Have Five Deputy Speakers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701145194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1419 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- Russian lower house 
speaker Ivan Rybkin will have five deputies, one of them will be 
first deputy, decided the lower house at its session on Monday 
[17 January]. 
  Russia's Choice faction nominated Mikhail Mityukov for the 
post of first deputy speaker. 
  Mityukov headed the committee on legislation for a long time 
at the disbanded Russian parliament. 
  Later in the day, the lower chamber approved the temporary 
regulations of the lower house council to be set up for "the 
preliminary discussion of organisational decisions on the 
procedure of the chamber's activities". 
  The council includes speaker as well as leaders of 
parliamentary factions and groups. The speaker informs 
legislators of all decisions by the council at the nearest 
session of the chamber. 
  The chamber may abrogate any decision taken by the council 
which meets every week. Any member of the lower chamber has the 
right to attend the council's meetings. 

</TEXT>

