<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Appointments; Communist Heads Security Committee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701170694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1630 
GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1701170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 17 Jan -- Communist Party representative 
Viktor Ilyukhin, who at one time tried to get Mikhail Gorbachev 
prosecuted for "betrayal of the motherland," was elected 
chairman of the State Duma Security Committee today. 
  Another key parliamentary post, that of chairman of the 
Defense Committee, went to Sergey Yushenkov of Russia's Choice. 
  There will be 23 committees in the Duma in all. Vladimir 
Isakov from the Agrarian Party has been elected chairman of the 
Committee on Legislative and Judicial Reform. In the last 
parliament he was one of the main opponents of presidential 
policy. 
  The Committee on the Budget, Taxation, Banking and Finance 
is 
headed by Mikhail Zadornov from the Yabloko bloc. Sergey 
Glazyev, who was recently forced to quit the post of minister 
for foreign economic relations, is chairman of the Committee for 
Economic Policy. He now represents the Democratic Party. 
  Vladimir Lukin, former Russian ambassador to the United 
States, from the Yabloko bloc, has become chairman of the 
Committee for International Affairs. 

</TEXT>

