<H3> <TI>   State Duma Refuses To Discuss Amnesty for Coups </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701125194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1221 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 17 TASS -- The Russian State Duma, 
the lower house of the parliament, turned down by a narrow 
margin on Monday [17 January] the proposal to include into the 
agenda the issue of an amnesty for organisers of the 1991 Soviet 
abortive coup and of the armed opposition revolt in Moscow in 
October 1993. 
  The proposal, made by lawmaker Vasiliy Lipitskiy, was 
supported by 205 votes and lacked just 18 votes for approval. 

</TEXT>

