<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Approves Procedures for Election of Speaker, Deputies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701205894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1956 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The State Duma has approved temporary regulations 
defining the procedure for electing the speaker, deputy speakers 
and their powers. 
  According to the regulations, the parliament elects one 
first 
deputy speaker and four deputy speakers. 
  The Duma Council consists of the parliamentary speaker and 
the heads of the parliamentary factions and deputies' groups. 
The council outlines a program for the session's work, a 
one-month timetable for consideration of issues included in the 
agenda and sends draft laws and resolutions to parliamentary 
committees. 
  The chairman of the chamber informs the deputies of all 
decisions made by the council. The State Duma may annul any 
decision made by the council. The Duma Council holds daily 
sessions. Any deputy of the State Duma is entitled to attend to 
the council's meetings. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

