<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Proposed Duma Rules Amendment Targets Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701222494 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
2020 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1701222494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Russia's Choice faction in the State Duma 
intends to submit to deputies the following amendment to the 
provisional standing orders: 
  A deputy who undermines the dignity of the State Duma 
through 
his speeches or actions will -- by the decision of the chamber 
-- be banned from participating in 10 of its sittings. 
  The faction has made this decision because on 13 January 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Liberal Democratic Party, 
used his speech from the podium to insult and directly threaten 
deputies. 
  The Russia's Choice amendment also states that if a deputy 
banned from participating in the chamber's sittings does not 
obey the decision, the chairman will be able to summon help from 
the security services. 

</TEXT>

