  [Text] The Russian Foreign Ministry issued a statement 
yesterday on Russian-Belarusian interstate relations. The 
document says that these remain priority relations for Russia, 
as they are aimed at fostering friendship and comprehensive 
political, economic, and humanitarian cooperation. According to 
a high-ranking Russian diplomat, the Russian Federation Foreign 
Ministry's statement is designed to assure the Belarusian side 
that earlier agreements between the two countries will not be 
revised depending on political expediency. 

