<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Meets Regional Heads </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401180994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1558 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- Russian Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin has met heads of executive power bodies from 
republics within the Russian Federation, territories, regions, 
autonomous formations and the cities of Moscow and St. 
Petersburg, head of the government press service Valentin 
Sergeyev said here today. 
  On proposal of Viktor Chernomyrdin, the meeting set up a 
commission to elaborate new principles of social-economic policy 
and forms of its implementation in Russian regions. The 
commission will be headed by Vice-Premier Yuriy Yarov and 
include Sergey Shakhray and representatives of all regional 
associations. 
  The commission will work to elaborate efficient mechanisms 
of 
interaction between the government and federal and regional 
authorities on principle of greater independence and expansion 
of rights of administration heads. 
  The commission's proposals will be considered by the 
government and reported to the Russian president. 
  The meeting showed Federation Council deputies are ready for 
active cooperation with the government of Viktor Chernomyrdin. 

</TEXT>

