<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Ossetia Prepares for Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1501204594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1724 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1501204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz January 15 TASS -- Northern Ossetia is 
getting ready for the elections of its first president on 
January 16. 
  Sources at the Central Electoral Commission told ITAR-TASS 
everything has been prepared. The ballot sheet includes names 
of two candidates -- that of North Ossetian Parliament Speaker 
Akhsarbek Galazov and Prime Minister Sergey Khetagurov; the rest 
four candidates quit the election campaign. 
  According to information of the North Ossetian Humanitarian 
Research Institute's sociology service, Galazov has the highest 
rating. 
  North Ossetian mass media circulated today a decree of the 
Russian president "on suspension of the state of emergency 
regime on part of territories of Northern Ossetia and 
Ingushetia." 
  The decree says the Russian president has decided to suspend 
from midnight of January 16 through midnight of January 17, 
1994, the validity of the state of emergency regime on part of 
Northern Ossetia and Ingushetia that has been prolonged by the 
Russian president's decree of November 30, 1993. A reason for 
this is the need to ensure citizens' right to vote during the 
elections of the North Ossetian president. 
  Allied forces attached to the temporary administration on 
territories of the Mozdok, Prigorodnyy regions and adjoining 
areas of Northern Ossetia and the Malgobek and Nazran regions of 
Ingushetia shall take measures to protect citizens and ensure 
order in public places. 
  The North Ossetian situation is relatively calm. Not a 
single inter-ethnic armed clash has been reported over the past 
24 hours. The Russian peace-makers together with the local 
law-enforcement bodies fully control the situation in the 
security zone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

