<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   President-Elect Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701100094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0907 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz January 17 TASS -- "I am grateful to 
the multinational people of North Ossetia for supporting my 
candidature during the election campaign and for voting for me 
at the January 16 elections," North Ossetian President-Elect 
Akhsarbek Galazov said in an interview with ITAR-TASS today. 
"The winners are above all, the sound forces who cherish the 
interests of peace and concord", he said. 
  "The elections of the president of the republic must 
consolidate the republic's multinational society, they must 
provide a positive impulse for the active implementation of 
reforms in the economy, social sphere and political life. Much 
work lies ahead, primarily associated with reforming state 
structures and local government bodies, the adoption of a new 
constitution of the Republic of North Ossetia. Everything must 
be done for the benefit of the people". 
  The Central Electoral Commission is now summarising the 
final 
results of the vote. According to preliminary data, about 
160,000 voters, or 66.3 per cent cast their ballots in favour of 
Galazov, while than 81,000 people (33.7 per cent) voted for his 
rival, government leader Sergey Khetagurov. 
  According to local observers, Akhsarbek Galazov was mainly 
supported by the masses of working people, veterans, teachers, 
scientists and cultural personalities. Sergey Khetagurov was 
mainly backed by industrialists, entrepreneurs and commercial 
structures. 
  Akhsarbek Galazov was born in 1929 in an old Ossetian 
village 
of Khumalag in the Pravoberezhniy district of North Ossetia. 
After graduating from a teacher-training institute, he taught 
Russian to schoolchildren. He then worked as an education 
ministry inspector, head of the teacher-retraining institute, 
the minister of education of North Ossetia and the chairman of 
the council of ministers. 
  From 1976 Akhsarbek Galazov worked as the rector of the 
North 
Ossetian State University. He is a professor who has written 
scientific works, manuals and monographs devoted to teaching and 
linguistics. From 1990 to 1991 Akhsarbek Galazov was the first 
secretary of the North Ossetian regional committee of the 
Communist Party of the Soviet Union. From 1990 he was chairman 
of the Supreme Soviet of the North Ossetian Soviet Socialist 
Republic (now the Republic of North Ossetia). 
  Akhsarbek Galazov has consistently advocated the concord and 
consolidation of all branches of power and a peaceful settlement 
of relations between North Ossetia and Ingushetia. 
  Last december he was elected to the Federation Council, the 
upper chamber of Russia's new legislature, the Federal Assembly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

