<H3> <TI>   Defeated Premier Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701110694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1701110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sergey Khetagurov, the head of the North Ossetian 
Government, announced his resignation at today's meeting of the 
Council of Ministers. He did so after the results of the 
election to choose the republic's first president were 
announced, RIA notes. Over 60 percent of the electorate cast 
their votes for his election rival, Akhsarbek Galazov, chairman 
of the North Ossetian Supreme Soviet. In accordance with the 
law on the president, Galazov is also head of the executive 
branch. He will shortly submit a new cabinet list to parliament. 

</TEXT>

