<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gives Reasons for Resignation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701143194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1337 
GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1701143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 17 Jan -- Sergey Khetagurov, chairman 
of the Council of Ministers of the republic of North Ossetia, 
who stood for president of the republic and lost in yesterday's 
election to the parliamentary leader Akhsarbek Galazov, resigned 
today. He explained his decision saying that "in the republic 
of North Ossetia, the president is the head of executive power 
and there cannot be two top figures of executive authority. It 
is a matter of honor for the loser to give way to the winner". 
  Sergey Khetagurov asked the members of the republic's 
Cabinet 
of Ministers to remain in their posts and carry out their duties 
until the new government is formed. 
  It is not yet known whether Akhsarbek Galazov, elected on 16 
January as the first president of the republic of North Ossetia, 
has accepted the resignation of Chairman of the Council of 
Ministers Sergey Khetagurov. 

</TEXT>

