<H3> <TI>   Final Results Issued </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801141594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1247 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz January 18 TASS -- 159,793 people (64 
per cent of the turnout) voted to elect Akhsarbek Galazov as 
president of the Russian Caucasian Republic of North Ossetia. 
81,386 people (32,6 per cent) voted for his rival Sergey 
Khetagurov, according to the final results of the election 
published on Tuesday. 
  Galazov held today a working meeting with lawmakers, members 
of the government and heads of the city and rural executive 
committees. He appealed to the members of the government to 
continue their duties until the new government would be formed. 
Khetagurov resigned as the prime minister. 
  The inauguration of the president is scheduled for January 
28, in accordance with the election law. 

</TEXT>

