<H3> <TI>   Resigns From Sverdlovsk Cabinet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1501121094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 15 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1501121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Irina Vladykina report from Yekaterinburg: "Resignation of </F>
Eduard Rossel's Cabinet"] 
  [Text] The Cabinet of the Sverdlovsk Oblast government, 
which was formed by Eduard Rossel and worked for a few years 
under him, has resigned in full strength. It was pointed out at 
a press conference that the decision was not related to the 
executive branch representatives' unwillingness to cooperate 
with the new chief of administration, nor was it a protest 
against his appointment. The government did so proceeding from 
generally applied standards: Once a chief is gone, his cabinet 
goes, too. The new governor has asked all members of the oblast 
administration to stay on until February, when a new Sverdlovsk 
Oblast government will be formed. 

</TEXT>

