<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Disagree Over Fedorov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801195494 Moscow Programma Radio Odin Network in Russian 
1900 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Programma Radio Odin Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The subject of the main disagreement during the 
meeting in the Kremlin between the president of the Russian 
Federation and Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, at which they 
discussed the composition of the government, was Boris Fedorov. 
An ITAR-TASS correspondent learned this from a high-ranking 
source in the president's apparatus. 
  The prime minister offered Boris Fedorov the post of finance 
minister in the reshuffled government. In response, Fedorov 
stipulated his conditions: the resignation of Deputy Prime 
Minister Aleksandr Zaveryukha and Central Bank Chairman Viktor 
Gerashchenko. According to the same source, Viktor Chernomyrdin 
and First Vice Premier Oleg Soskovets did not accept Boris 
Fedorov's demands. As a result, Boris Fedorov announced his 
resignation. Thus, the composition of the government remains 
unknown. 

</TEXT>

