<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Consultations To Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901145294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1400 GMT 
19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Consultations between the Russian president and the 
prime minister on the composition of the reshuffled government 
may continue until the end of this week, INTERFAX was told today 
by a source within the administration of the head of state which 
wishes to remain anonymous. 
  The source maintains that differences between Boris Yeltsin 
and Viktor Chernomyrdin on a number of candidacies for key 
Cabinet posts presented to the prime minister have somewhat 
delayed a decision on the Cabinet's personal composition. 
  The source offered the following rough forecast: 
Chernomyrdin 
as the prime minister, Oleg Soskovets as the first deputy prime 
minister, Chubays, Fedorov, Yarov, Zaveryukha as deputy prime 
ministers, Grachev, Yerin, and Kozyrev as ministers in charge of 
decision-making ministries, and Gerashchenko, as chairman of the 
Central Bank. 

</TEXT>

