<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fedorov Seeks To Retain Deputy Premiership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801164694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1600 GMT 
18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Boris Fedorov, on whom so much attention was focused 
today, the meeting between the Russian leaders included, told 
Valentin Sergeyev, head of the Russian Government press service 
that he had not resigned from the post of Deputy Prime Minister, 
but only from the post of Finance Minister. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

