<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Has Not Accepted Finance Minister Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801180194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1731 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Tamara Zamyatina and Ivan </F>
Ivanov] 
  [Text] Moscow January 18 TASS -- Russia's new government 
composition is still unclear after six hours of non-stop talks 
between President Boris Yeltsin and Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin. 
  According to a reliable source, no documents shaping out a 
new cabinet have been signed yet. 
  Conflicting media reports on Boris Fedorov's stance were 
clarified to some extent by Valentin Sergeyev, chief of the 
governmental press service. He quoted Fedorov as telling him by 
telephone at 15:30 today that he has "not formally asked to 
resign as a vice-premier". But he has "not accepted the 
prime-minister's offer to hold the post of finance minister in 
the reformed cabinet", Fedorov was quoted as saying. 

</TEXT>

